2
00:00:01.500 --> 00:00:03.480
US, US

3
00:00:04.100 --> 00:00:09.340
US, ALL OF US

4
00:00:12.970 --> 00:00:15.770
The end of the dream, the end of the sea

5
00:00:15.770 --> 00:00:18.530
We all have different places we want to go

6
00:00:16.370 --> 00:00:17.750
We all have different places we want to go WE ALL HAVE DIFFERENT PLACES WE WANT TO GO

7
00:00:18.530 --> 00:00:21.310
But to start we've got to show what we're made of

8
00:00:21.310 --> 00:00:25.660
We'll be legends, we're gonna take the world by storm

9
00:00:26.930 --> 00:00:29.250
Sparks are flying, NO LIMITS! This is where it starts

10
00:00:29.250 --> 00:00:30.530
ONE PIECE!!

11
00:00:30.890 --> 00:00:33.510
ALL OF US, I've got a question for you
VORONOI START VORONOI END ALL OF US, I've got a question for you

12
00:00:33.510 --> 00:00:37.100
Have you let the world and all its burdens bring your dreams down?

13
00:00:38.740 --> 00:00:45.300
Every cell in me is getting restless - They're about to blow, oh, it's just too much Every cell in me is getting restless - They're about to blow, oh, it's just too much

14
00:00:45.410 --> 00:00:52.030
Still we try, ALL OF US have our own paths we cling to

15
00:00:52.030 --> 00:00:54.620
ALL OF US, I've got something to tell you

16
00:00:53.620 --> 00:00:55.150
ALL OF US, I've got something to tell you If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall

17
00:00:54.680 --> 00:00:58.200
If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall

18
00:00:59.890 --> 00:01:02.580
Random clues suddenly fit together

19
00:01:02.580 --> 00:01:06.510
Starting to make sense, oh, what's going on?

20
00:01:06.510 --> 00:01:12.980
Threads of time weaving into an intricate tapestry

21
00:01:13.070 --> 00:01:18.680
We can't stop the world from turning, it's changing along with every one of-

22
00:01:19.280 --> 00:01:21.250
US, US

23
00:01:21.870 --> 00:01:26.360
US, ALL OF US

24
00:01:30.070 --> 00:01:35.360
<b>Marine Headquarters</b>

25
00:01:31.150 --> 00:01:33.820
A figure beloved by Marines and citizens alike,

26
00:01:33.820 --> 00:01:38.950
<b>Vice Admiral T-Bone Dead</b>

27
00:01:33.820 --> 00:01:39.250
Vice Admiral T-Bone's death in the line
of duty was a shock to the public.

28
00:01:35.360 --> 00:01:38.490
<b>Marine Headquarters</b>

29
00:01:39.250 --> 00:01:43.210
However, the Marines never revealed
the cause of his death.

30
00:01:39.790 --> 00:01:43.210
<b>Marine Headquarters 
Vice Admiral T-Bone Dead</b>

31
00:01:43.250 --> 00:01:48.050
<b>Let's Go and Take It!</b>

32
00:01:44.080 --> 00:01:46.210
Have we found the culprit?

33
00:01:46.590 --> 00:01:48.210
I have no idea.

34
00:01:48.210 --> 00:01:52.380
All I know is that the killer's family
must be living a happy life now.

35
00:01:53.220 --> 00:01:55.600
The world is going to the dogs, Tsuru.

36
00:01:55.970 --> 00:02:00.140
What do you do when the very citizens
you've sworn to protect stab you in the back?

37
00:02:00.140 --> 00:02:02.600
Once you have bounties put out on Marines,

38
00:02:03.100 --> 00:02:06.730
it's no longer just pirates
who want a piece of that pie.

39
00:02:06.730 --> 00:02:11.570
He was murdered in the Pepe Kingdom, where
starvation claims over a thousand lives each year.

40
00:02:12.320 --> 00:02:15.160
Poverty and wealth change people...

41
00:02:15.160 --> 00:02:17.950
not to make excuses for the killer.

42
00:02:17.950 --> 00:02:22.160
If this is what he was after,
then we underestimated the Bombastic Clown.

43
00:02:22.160 --> 00:02:27.380
How can we risk our lives for civilians
who might kill us at any moment?

44
00:02:29.250 --> 00:02:31.300
If we don't take down Cross Guild soon...

45
00:02:32.510 --> 00:02:37.720
it could demoralize the rank and file
and weaken our organization!

46
00:02:35.680 --> 00:02:36.390
<b>Marine Headquarters 
Vice Admiral T-Bone Dead</b>

47
00:02:40.190 --> 00:02:41.390
Hina!

48
00:02:42.020 --> 00:02:43.890
Do you know where Garp is?

49
00:02:43.890 --> 00:02:46.520
I've got a new rice cracker
flavor for him to try.

50
00:02:46.520 --> 00:02:47.730
Oh, yeah...

51
00:02:47.730 --> 00:02:51.690
He said he was going to go save Koby
a few days ago, so...

52
00:02:51.690 --> 00:02:54.240
he's probably with SWORD right now.

53
00:02:54.240 --> 00:02:55.950
Kujaku is probably with him, too.

54
00:02:56.320 --> 00:02:57.200
– What?!
– What?!

55
00:02:57.950 --> 00:03:01.450
– They went to Beehive?!
– They went to Beehive?!

56
00:03:04.210 --> 00:03:06.960
<b>Empty Bluffs Island
New World</b>

57
00:03:06.960 --> 00:03:10.130
I'm impressed you made it
all the way across the sea!

58
00:03:10.130 --> 00:03:11.170
Thank you...

59
00:03:11.170 --> 00:03:13.380
Well done indeed!

60
00:03:13.380 --> 00:03:16.220
The kingpins of the underworld are pleased!

61
00:03:16.630 --> 00:03:19.050
This is your big debut as a criminal rock star!

62
00:03:22.890 --> 00:03:26.770
I was told that my family
received the money...

63
00:03:26.770 --> 00:03:28.600
Thank you so much!

64
00:03:28.600 --> 00:03:30.610
Of course they did!

65
00:03:30.610 --> 00:03:36.320
You're the evil mastermind who took out
none other than a vice admiral from Marine HQ!

66
00:03:39.660 --> 00:03:43.290
I heard the Marines
lost their minds the day it happened!

67
00:03:43.290 --> 00:03:47.920
If they ever find you,
your head's coming right off!

68
00:03:50.500 --> 00:03:53.630
I thought that even if I could
never see my family again,

69
00:03:54.260 --> 00:03:56.970
this was still better than letting them starve!

70
00:03:56.970 --> 00:03:58.720
Not to worry!

71
00:03:58.720 --> 00:04:02.310
I'll take you in as part of my pirate crew!

72
00:04:02.310 --> 00:04:03.600
Pirate crew?

73
00:04:03.600 --> 00:04:05.810
Welcome aboard, newbie!

74
00:04:05.810 --> 00:04:07.390
No, I...

75
00:04:07.390 --> 00:04:09.400
You don't get it, do you?

76
00:04:09.400 --> 00:04:10.270
Huh?

77
00:04:10.270 --> 00:04:13.110
President Buggy, the Bombastic Clown,
is an Emperor!

78
00:04:13.110 --> 00:04:18.110
Your average pirate could only
dream of meeting someone like him!

79
00:04:18.110 --> 00:04:20.320
Make sure you get a good look!
'Cause that's...

80
00:04:20.320 --> 00:04:22.740
President Buggy in the flesh!

81
00:04:24.620 --> 00:04:26.200
Buggy in the flesh!

82
00:04:26.200 --> 00:04:28.210
– Buggy in the flesh!
– Buggy in the flesh!

83
00:04:28.210 --> 00:04:30.290
I love it, guys!

84
00:04:28.210 --> 00:04:31.710
– Buggy in the flesh! Buggy in the flesh!
– Buggy in the flesh! Buggy in the flesh!

85
00:04:31.710 --> 00:04:33.210
– Buggy in the flesh!
– Buggy in the flesh!

86
00:04:33.210 --> 00:04:36.670
– Buggy in the flesh! Buggy in the flesh!
– Buggy in the flesh! Buggy in the flesh!

87
00:04:36.670 --> 00:04:39.590
– Buggy in the flesh!
– Buggy in the flesh!

88
00:04:38.840 --> 00:04:41.140
Excuse me, President Baggy Flesh!

89
00:04:41.140 --> 00:04:43.220
Whose flesh is baggy?!

90
00:04:43.550 --> 00:04:45.430
Presenting...

91
00:04:45.430 --> 00:04:47.930
Cross Guild's ship!

92
00:04:48.640 --> 00:04:50.770
Let me take care of the ship!

93
00:04:50.770 --> 00:04:53.360
We've got some amazing shipwrights!

94
00:04:55.940 --> 00:04:56.780
Why?!

95
00:04:56.780 --> 00:04:58.280
What the hell is this?!

96
00:04:58.280 --> 00:05:00.660
Gotta have President Buggy on the front, duh!

97
00:05:00.660 --> 00:05:01.780
Pretty good, huh?!

98
00:05:01.780 --> 00:05:03.240
It's the bestest ship ever!

99
00:05:03.240 --> 00:05:05.490
Great work, everyone!

100
00:05:03.990 --> 00:05:06.700
P-Please stop...

101
00:05:09.540 --> 00:05:12.290
Hey, what the hell is that?

102
00:05:12.290 --> 00:05:17.130
We are not sailing on that hideous thing.

103
00:05:17.130 --> 00:05:18.800
Meeting room. Now!

104
00:05:20.300 --> 00:05:23.300
W-W-Wait... This isn't...

105
00:05:29.850 --> 00:05:32.770
<b>Meeting Room</b>

106
00:05:30.980 --> 00:05:34.310
The public reception to
Cross Guild has been excellent.

107
00:05:34.810 --> 00:05:38.860
It's about time for the Marines
to notice the threat we pose.

108
00:05:39.240 --> 00:05:43.160
Just... Just... kill me already...

109
00:05:43.160 --> 00:05:44.200
I can't take any more...

110
00:05:44.200 --> 00:05:46.330
We must establish a utopia,

111
00:05:46.330 --> 00:05:51.250
a military nation that can face
any amount of opposition.

112
00:05:51.830 --> 00:05:53.790
And that's going to take...

113
00:05:54.170 --> 00:05:55.750
...overwhelming power.

114
00:05:55.750 --> 00:05:57.670
This is all wrong...

115
00:05:57.670 --> 00:06:01.880
This isn't how my life was supposed to go...

116
00:06:01.880 --> 00:06:04.590
And to afford that, we'll need tremendous...

117
00:06:04.590 --> 00:06:06.390
...wealth and power, right?!

118
00:06:07.850 --> 00:06:09.600
P-Pardon the interruption...

119
00:06:09.600 --> 00:06:10.810
Be quiet.

120
00:06:12.270 --> 00:06:16.440
Come on, if you're gonna
kill me, just do it already!

121
00:06:16.440 --> 00:06:19.110
But seriously, how can you
call yourselves pirates?!

122
00:06:19.110 --> 00:06:21.440
You're not thinking big enough!

123
00:06:21.440 --> 00:06:24.530
Stop taking such a roundabout approach!

124
00:06:24.530 --> 00:06:26.120
What is this? Desperation?

125
00:06:26.490 --> 00:06:31.120
I'm sure you've heard that
Red Hair is on the move.

126
00:06:31.120 --> 00:06:34.710
Even though we were both
on the Pirate King's crew,

127
00:06:35.290 --> 00:06:39.000
for one reason or another,
neither of us ever made it to Laugh Tale.

128
00:06:39.380 --> 00:06:42.970
What did you guys want to become
when you were young?!

129
00:06:42.970 --> 00:06:47.930
When I saw the sort of potential Shanks had...

130
00:06:47.930 --> 00:06:51.350
I gave up on my own dream!

131
00:06:52.100 --> 00:06:53.810
<b>24 Years Ago

The Day of
Gold Roger's Execution</b>

132
00:06:54.190 --> 00:06:57.060
Don't you remember what you said, Shanks?!

133
00:06:57.060 --> 00:07:00.230
You said you'd sail your own ship
to Laugh Tale one day!

134
00:07:00.570 --> 00:07:01.860
Yeah.

135
00:07:01.860 --> 00:07:03.490
But I've changed my mind.

136
00:07:03.490 --> 00:07:05.450
I'm not going for it right now.

137
00:07:05.450 --> 00:07:06.910
What?!

138
00:07:06.910 --> 00:07:08.660
I'm going to stay a pirate, though.

139
00:07:08.660 --> 00:07:11.580
I'm disappointed in you, Shanks.

140
00:07:11.620 --> 00:07:16.040
You were supposed to become
the king of the next generation.

141
00:07:16.620 --> 00:07:19.130
Come with me, Buggy.

142
00:07:19.840 --> 00:07:22.960
I'm not gonna take orders from you, dumbass!

143
00:07:22.960 --> 00:07:24.220
You're a coward!

144
00:07:24.720 --> 00:07:29.850
Captain Roger wanted you
to follow in his footsteps, didn't he?!

145
00:07:29.850 --> 00:07:32.100
You better not have forgotten!

146
00:07:32.470 --> 00:07:34.850
You're the reason I lost my treasure map!

147
00:07:34.850 --> 00:07:36.480
I haven't forgiven you for that!

148
00:07:36.480 --> 00:07:41.110
The next time we meet, we'll be enemies!

149
00:07:41.360 --> 00:07:43.440
And now Shanks is on the move.

150
00:07:43.440 --> 00:07:46.110
Why, after all these years?!

151
00:07:46.110 --> 00:07:48.070
But this time...!

152
00:07:48.070 --> 00:07:51.660
Call it an accident or just dumb luck,
but I'm on the same level as he is!

153
00:07:54.040 --> 00:07:58.870
So... I wanna be the King of the Pirates!

154
00:07:58.870 --> 00:08:01.130
Power?! Wealth?!

155
00:08:01.130 --> 00:08:02.460
We can have it all!

156
00:08:06.420 --> 00:08:08.380
Let's go and take it!

157
00:08:08.380 --> 00:08:11.140
The greatest treasure in the world!

158
00:08:13.890 --> 00:08:16.180
Shut the hell up!

159
00:08:16.930 --> 00:08:17.890
Oh crap!

160
00:08:29.530 --> 00:08:33.030
I know titles tend to go to people's heads,

161
00:08:33.030 --> 00:08:35.240
but can you seriously be this delusional?!

162
00:08:35.620 --> 00:08:39.120
Did you think we would be so easily
swayed by your glib tongue?

163
00:08:39.120 --> 00:08:41.540
No plan, no preparation...

164
00:08:41.540 --> 00:08:43.460
Piracy is a business!

165
00:08:43.460 --> 00:08:46.300
Red Hair, Blackbeard, Straw Hat...

166
00:08:46.300 --> 00:08:49.050
Do you intend for us to fight them all?

167
00:08:49.800 --> 00:08:51.640
We just gotta beat them to the punch!

168
00:08:51.640 --> 00:08:54.600
A treasure hunt is a race after all!

169
00:08:55.810 --> 00:08:58.060
Allow me to demonstrate!

170
00:08:58.060 --> 00:09:00.900
Remember the passion that these words inspire!

171
00:09:00.900 --> 00:09:03.520
All pirates...

172
00:09:03.520 --> 00:09:06.980
set out to sea in search of the same thing!

173
00:09:09.320 --> 00:09:11.990
Listen up, you guys!

174
00:09:12.950 --> 00:09:14.780
– President Buggy?
– President Buggy?

175
00:09:15.700 --> 00:09:18.160
That's enough, Buggy!

176
00:09:23.040 --> 00:09:24.710
Tell me!

177
00:09:24.710 --> 00:09:27.840
What was the dream
that drove you to sea?!

178
00:09:28.340 --> 00:09:31.300
Out here, where you could
die at any moment...

179
00:09:31.300 --> 00:09:35.810
does your soul not cry out for it?!

180
00:09:45.110 --> 00:09:46.230
It's happening!

181
00:09:46.230 --> 00:09:50.070
President Buggy is reigniting
the lost passion within our hearts!

182
00:09:50.070 --> 00:09:53.280
To all the cowards who have grown
content with the status quo...

183
00:09:53.280 --> 00:09:56.910
reach out for what your heart desires the most!

184
00:09:56.910 --> 00:09:59.620
Remember, you've got me at your side!

185
00:10:03.580 --> 00:10:05.330
Let's go and take...

186
00:10:05.330 --> 00:10:07.250
the One Piece!

187
00:10:10.420 --> 00:10:11.130
Hey!

188
00:10:12.090 --> 00:10:14.510
– The One Piece!
– The One Piece!

189
00:10:20.310 --> 00:10:21.930
Whose ship is it?

190
00:10:21.930 --> 00:10:24.770
<b>Deputy Commander Ushiano
(Morley's Subordinate)
Western Division
Revolutionary Army</b>

191
00:10:21.930 --> 00:10:23.060
Almost there!

192
00:10:23.060 --> 00:10:23.940
Too steep?

193
00:10:23.940 --> 00:10:24.770
You okay?

194
00:10:26.650 --> 00:10:29.110
<b>Kamabakka Queendom
Grand Line</b>

195
00:10:30.110 --> 00:10:32.570
<b>Deputy Commander Ahiru
(Belo Betty's Subordinate)
Eastern Division
Revolutionary Army</b>

196
00:10:37.200 --> 00:10:39.740
<b>Deputy Commander Jiron
(Karasu's Subordinate)
Northern Division
Revolutionary Army</b>

197
00:10:41.330 --> 00:10:43.460
Hey! So?! So?!

198
00:10:43.460 --> 00:10:45.540
So, that ship...

199
00:10:45.540 --> 00:10:48.170
Is it an enemy? What? Who?
What should we do?!

200
00:10:48.540 --> 00:10:51.300
Hey! It's coming this way!

201
00:10:51.300 --> 00:10:52.630
Be quiet.

202
00:10:53.220 --> 00:10:54.840
Whoosh...

203
00:10:57.600 --> 00:10:58.550
Whiiir.

204
00:10:58.550 --> 00:10:59.970
Ka-chunk!

205
00:10:59.970 --> 00:11:01.020
Shwing!

206
00:11:07.270 --> 00:11:09.400
Hey, wanna make a bet?

207
00:11:10.320 --> 00:11:15.240
<b>Deputy Commander Gambo
(Lindbergh's Subordinate)
Southern Division
Revolutionary Army</b>

208
00:11:10.320 --> 00:11:12.650
On the unknown ship?

209
00:11:12.650 --> 00:11:14.400
I bet it's an enemy ship!

210
00:11:14.400 --> 00:11:15.240
So, how much?

211
00:11:16.700 --> 00:11:18.410
Sure!

212
00:11:19.410 --> 00:11:21.660
Bweee...

213
00:11:25.830 --> 00:11:27.460
I'll bet...

214
00:11:29.380 --> 00:11:32.340
a million on Sabo's return.

215
00:11:32.340 --> 00:11:34.170
What?!

216
00:11:34.170 --> 00:11:35.300
A million?!

217
00:11:47.270 --> 00:11:48.900
Dragon!

218
00:11:48.900 --> 00:11:50.400
Iva!

219
00:11:50.400 --> 00:11:52.360
Sabo...

220
00:11:52.360 --> 00:11:55.240
has returned!

221
00:11:57.030 --> 00:11:59.030
Heehaw!

222
00:11:59.030 --> 00:12:00.700
Vhaat a relief!

223
00:12:00.700 --> 00:12:02.870
So he is alright!

224
00:12:05.200 --> 00:12:07.580
I missed him so much!

225
00:12:07.580 --> 00:12:09.170
– Sabo!
– Sabo!

226
00:12:25.310 --> 00:12:26.930
Sabo!

227
00:12:46.200 --> 00:12:47.580
Everyone!

228
00:12:47.580 --> 00:12:48.960
I'm back!

229
00:12:49.870 --> 00:12:52.960
– Welcome back, Sabo!
– Welcome back, Sabo!

230
00:12:54.880 --> 00:12:56.260
I know you cheated!

231
00:12:56.260 --> 00:12:57.760
A million?!

232
00:12:57.760 --> 00:12:59.550
You won't get one berry out of me!

233
00:12:59.550 --> 00:13:02.760
Nah, I'll make you pay.

234
00:13:02.760 --> 00:13:03.720
Huh?

235
00:13:03.720 --> 00:13:06.470
You used a telescope, didn't you?!

236
00:13:06.470 --> 00:13:07.850
Nope.

237
00:13:07.850 --> 00:13:09.230
Are you eating it?!

238
00:13:09.230 --> 00:13:10.600
Where's the telescope?!

239
00:13:10.980 --> 00:13:12.770
Whiiir.

240
00:13:12.770 --> 00:13:13.730
Ka-chunk!

241
00:13:15.320 --> 00:13:16.440
Welcome back!

242
00:13:16.440 --> 00:13:18.150
I almost shot you, Sabo!

243
00:13:18.150 --> 00:13:20.650
You're a menace, Ahiru.

244
00:13:20.650 --> 00:13:21.860
Did I make you worry?

245
00:13:21.860 --> 00:13:23.200
Maybe!

246
00:13:23.200 --> 00:13:25.910
Sabo! Safe! Happy!

247
00:13:25.910 --> 00:13:28.830
I'm happy to see you too, Ushiano.

248
00:13:28.830 --> 00:13:30.040
Honestly, now!

249
00:13:30.040 --> 00:13:32.420
You certainly like to keep people in suspense!

250
00:13:32.420 --> 00:13:35.170
You had us vorried sick!

251
00:13:35.170 --> 00:13:36.380
Sorry about that.

252
00:13:37.000 --> 00:13:39.920
Vhaat took you so long, anyway?

253
00:13:39.920 --> 00:13:42.130
This is a Lulusian ship.

254
00:13:42.470 --> 00:13:44.390
The kingdom that suddenly vanished?!

255
00:13:44.390 --> 00:13:44.970
Yeah.

256
00:13:45.300 --> 00:13:46.720
I'll explain later.

257
00:13:48.890 --> 00:13:52.020
Let's get them settled in first.

258
00:13:52.600 --> 00:13:54.560
Sabo!

259
00:13:58.110 --> 00:14:00.530
How could you just go radio silent?!

260
00:14:00.530 --> 00:14:02.240
Koala, I'm sorry!

261
00:14:04.160 --> 00:14:06.450
I didn't have an encryption transponder snail,

262
00:14:06.450 --> 00:14:09.750
so all my communications
would have been intercepted!

263
00:14:10.200 --> 00:14:13.960
But I gave it the triple tap
to signal it was an indirect call!

264
00:14:14.460 --> 00:14:16.460
I wasn't in Lulusia.

265
00:14:17.000 --> 00:14:18.000
Still...

266
00:14:21.010 --> 00:14:24.970
I was worried about you!

267
00:14:25.470 --> 00:14:26.970
Sorry.

268
00:14:35.350 --> 00:14:37.560
Sabo!

269
00:14:37.560 --> 00:14:39.530
Seriously...

270
00:14:39.530 --> 00:14:42.030
why are you boys all like this?!

271
00:14:43.400 --> 00:14:44.240
Morley!

272
00:14:44.240 --> 00:14:48.830
Don't make me worry!

273
00:14:48.830 --> 00:14:51.450
Sabo!

274
00:14:52.080 --> 00:14:56.170
I'm so glad you're back!

275
00:14:58.130 --> 00:14:59.340
Welcome!

276
00:15:01.130 --> 00:15:04.010
I remember you bozos from Lulusia!

277
00:15:04.720 --> 00:15:07.090
Sorry about what happened to your home.

278
00:15:07.720 --> 00:15:10.720
I heard you wanted to join
the Revolutionary Army.

279
00:15:10.720 --> 00:15:12.720
– Yes! That's right!
– Yes! That's right!

280
00:15:12.720 --> 00:15:13.560
But first!

281
00:15:14.180 --> 00:15:15.560
Go get some rest.

282
00:15:16.190 --> 00:15:18.060
Take some time and clear your heads.

283
00:15:23.990 --> 00:15:25.950
I heard about Kuma.

284
00:15:25.950 --> 00:15:27.160
My apologies.

285
00:15:27.160 --> 00:15:29.870
All your efforts have gone to waste.

286
00:15:29.870 --> 00:15:36.330
He may have been programmed
to return to Mary Geoise at any moment.

287
00:15:36.330 --> 00:15:37.830
No...

288
00:15:37.830 --> 00:15:41.250
It must be harder on you two than it is on me.

289
00:15:41.250 --> 00:15:45.970
Sabo... not even the captains
can hear vhaat you have to say?

290
00:15:46.380 --> 00:15:47.470
Yeah...

291
00:15:47.470 --> 00:15:51.430
Just knowing this could endanger their lives.

292
00:15:51.430 --> 00:15:52.260
Vhaat is it?

293
00:15:53.100 --> 00:15:56.100
This year's Reverie
was particularly tumultuous...

294
00:15:56.480 --> 00:15:59.980
I'll tell you everything that actually happened...

295
00:15:59.980 --> 00:16:01.900
at the Holy Land, Mary Geoise!

296
00:16:01.900 --> 00:16:04.320
We accomplished every aspect of our mission.

297
00:16:05.900 --> 00:16:08.530
We had three main objectives:

298
00:16:09.160 --> 00:16:12.780
Declare war by destroying
the symbol of the Celestial Dragons.

299
00:16:13.410 --> 00:16:17.660
Free as many slaves as possible
while rescuing Kuma.

300
00:16:18.290 --> 00:16:21.630
And finally, destroy the food reserves
in the Land of the Gods.

301
00:16:22.250 --> 00:16:23.500
How did it turn out?

302
00:16:23.500 --> 00:16:24.710
Well...

303
00:16:25.090 --> 00:16:28.180
You certainly caught the world's attention.

304
00:16:28.180 --> 00:16:33.060
Thanks to the fact that you kept
a majority of the Marine forces occupied,

305
00:16:33.060 --> 00:16:39.140
twelve countries revolted
because of our influence.

306
00:16:39.480 --> 00:16:44.020
Eight of those revolutions were successful.

307
00:16:44.530 --> 00:16:47.610
They dubbed it the Eight-Nation Revolution,

308
00:16:47.610 --> 00:16:50.990
but one of the countries,
the Kingdom of Lulusia...

309
00:16:51.990 --> 00:16:53.700
mysteriously vanished.

310
00:16:56.200 --> 00:16:58.410
The newspapers haven't reported this yet,

311
00:16:58.790 --> 00:17:01.540
but the seven remaining nations that revolted

312
00:17:01.540 --> 00:17:04.670
are declining to pay the heavenly tribute

313
00:17:04.670 --> 00:17:07.920
and have stopped exporting resources
to the government.

314
00:17:08.380 --> 00:17:13.050
The Revolutionary Army is carrying out
global attacks on the government's supply lines,

315
00:17:13.050 --> 00:17:16.270
cutting off resources from Mary Geoise!

316
00:17:16.270 --> 00:17:20.230
<b>The Holy Land
Mary Geoise</b>

317
00:17:16.810 --> 00:17:21.730
People say Mary Geoise is an impregnable
fortress because it is high above the sea.

318
00:17:22.690 --> 00:17:25.690
But they cannot viithstand
our starvation tactics!

319
00:17:25.690 --> 00:17:29.780
Let them learn vhaat it means
to be poor and go hungry!

320
00:17:30.030 --> 00:17:32.570
Heehaw!

321
00:17:33.780 --> 00:17:35.530
We can expect a reaction, right?

322
00:17:36.030 --> 00:17:38.410
Yes, it's highly likely.

323
00:17:38.410 --> 00:17:46.630
Not everything is being interrupted,
but it's a death by a thousand cuts.

324
00:17:47.670 --> 00:17:52.510
Of course, they aren't the sort of people
to take this lying down.

325
00:17:52.510 --> 00:17:57.470
Once they dispatch the Holy Knights,
the real battle will begin!

326
00:17:57.470 --> 00:17:58.430
Sabo!

327
00:17:58.810 --> 00:18:01.230
No... Flame Emperor boy!

328
00:18:01.560 --> 00:18:04.860
You are their number one target now!

329
00:18:04.860 --> 00:18:07.610
I still don't like that nickname...

330
00:18:07.610 --> 00:18:11.070
Be that as it may, it has
made you a household name.

331
00:18:11.070 --> 00:18:18.790
Regardless of the truth, the assassination
of King Cobra made you a hero.

332
00:18:21.040 --> 00:18:24.420
From the perspective of the insurgents,

333
00:18:24.420 --> 00:18:28.550
anyone affiliated with
the World Government is the same.

334
00:18:28.550 --> 00:18:32.720
Of course, there are some kings
who have mistreated their people,

335
00:18:32.720 --> 00:18:36.430
but there are many
just and capable kings as well.

336
00:18:37.890 --> 00:18:45.850
Even among them, King Cobra of Alabasta was
known as an outstanding and benevolent monarch.

337
00:18:46.360 --> 00:18:49.820
But what gets reported
does not always reflect reality.

338
00:18:50.190 --> 00:18:51.280
Well...

339
00:18:51.820 --> 00:18:53.450
it doesn't bother me.

340
00:18:53.990 --> 00:18:56.240
What happened to King Cobra is a tragedy...

341
00:18:56.620 --> 00:19:00.200
but it's all to stoke the flames of revolution!

342
00:19:01.290 --> 00:19:02.910
That's why we put our faith in you.

343
00:19:03.750 --> 00:19:06.960
Now, let us hear it!

